main event: An unidentified aerial object observed in Dayton, Ohio on 18 February 1965.
interesting points: The object was described as satellite-like but did not behave like a satellite,It was observed at an elevation of about 30 degrees moving northwest before climbing to 65 degrees,The object displayed green flashing lights and traveled at high speeds,Witnesses initially thought it was a satellite due to its appearance before realizing it behaved unusually,The sighting lasted for about 55-60 seconds.
witness description: The object appeared bright, rotating, and would vanish and reappear during the observation.
